#: ../../firewall_rules.rst:8 990c153e96c547209b3992351d78749d
msgid ""
"Firewall rules define how network traffic is segmented and controlled "
"between different zones. Firewalls acts as barriers between trusted "
"internal networks and untrusted external networks, such as the internet. "
"These rules specify which traffic is allowed, denied, or monitored based "
"on predefined security policies."
msgstr ""

#: ../../firewall_rules.rst:12 ae02ac05a3924af1ae7a1a19304f452c
msgid ""
"The order of rules is important; the first matching rule is applied, "
"determining the fate of the network packet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../firewall_rules.rst:14 bc460760f8244772acd94baaf0700b76
msgid "The page is organized into three tabs, each serving a specific purpose:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../firewall_rules.rst:16 c41eea19f41d44ae9eb5024b7a7708ef
msgid ""
"``Forward rules`` tab: this tab is dedicated to configuring rules for "
"data packets moving between different zones in the network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../firewall_rules.rst:17 daa26150d9274023b8381a1b1de09326
msgid ""
"``Input rules`` tab: this tab is dedicated to configuring rules for "
"incoming packets destined for the firewall itself."
msgstr ""

#: ../../firewall_rules.rst:18 14880ab9a4ab4b05bb1e18f1143f3381
msgid ""
"``Output rules`` tab: this tab is dedicated to configuring rules for "
"packets emitted by the firewall."
msgstr ""

#: ../../firewall_rules.rst:20 6eaa411da3594f369c9a9f5a3584785f
msgid ""
"Locate the button to add a new rule, click on it to initiate the rule "
"creation process. Fill in the following fields for the new rule:"
